title: Stryker Earnings, Revenue Beat in Q3
text:
Investing.com - Stryker (NYSE:SYK) reported third quarter earnings that beat analysts' expectations on Tuesday and revenue that topped forecasts.

The firm reported earnings per share of $1.91 on revenue of $3.59B. Analysts polled by Investing.com expected EPS of $1.9 on revenue of $3.58B. That compared to EPS of $1.69 on revenue of $3.24B in the same period a year earlier. The company had reported EPS of $1.98 on revenue of $3.65B in the previous quarter.





Stryker follows other major Healthcare sector earnings this month

On October 15, J&J reported third quarter EPS of $2.12 on revenue of $20.73B, compared to forecasts of EPS of $2.01 on revenue of $20.08B.

Merck&Co earnings beat analysts' expectations on Tuesday, with third quarter EPS of $1.51 on revenue of $12.4B. Investing.com analysts expected EPS of $1.24 on revenue of $11.65B
